The expression statement "(void) cls;" is an executed no-op whose removal would not affect program behaviour. It simply discards the value of cls to silence a compiler warning, but cls is otherwise used in the function (and even if it were unused, the cast has no side-effects). This is executed code with no effect and therefore constitutes dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
